verbose_text: In the present study, it was found that miR-143-3p upregulation significantly suppressed OSCC cell proliferation, induced apoptosis, and effectively suppressed the migration and invasion of OSCC cells by gain-of-function experiments, which is consistent with the findings of a previous study.
